<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,613,784]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,649,675]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</emphasis>
Females of the sexual generation were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[932,1111,649,676]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="24 - 38" refId="ref48573" refString="Monzen, K. (1954) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (II). Cynipidae (Cynipinae) Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of Gakugei Faculty of Iwate University, 6, 24 - 38." type="journal article" year="1954">Monzen (1954)</bibRefCitation>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa and Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
described the galls of the asexual generation (C-125) and experimentally closed the alternating lifecycle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,613,784]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,721,747]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Biology.</emphasis>
The catkin galls of the sexual generation and the bud galls of the asexual generation both develop on 
<taxonomicName box="[151,480,757,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mongolica" subSpecies="crispula">
<emphasis box="[151,303,757,784]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Q. mongolica</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[388,480,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">crispula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[535,650,758,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[535,650,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Q. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName box="[689,861,757,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulifera">
<emphasis box="[689,861,757,784]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Q. glandulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1039,758,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[945,1039,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[1162,1320,757,784]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="24 - 38" refId="ref48573" refString="Monzen, K. (1954) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (II). Cynipidae (Cynipinae) Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of Gakugei Faculty of Iwate University, 6, 24 - 38." type="journal article" year="1954">Monzen 1954</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
